{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_3","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-14-no-editor-task1-review.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Evolution Note — No Editor Task1 Review\n\n## Plan\n\n- path: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- milestone: `Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer (complete)`\n- bounded target: review whether Task 1 now keeps the smallest board-card operations inside the managed center after restoring the prompt entry point\n\n## Completed\n\n- Re-read `ROADMAP.md`, `task-plans/no-editor-first-workflows-task-plan.md`, `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`, and the latest relevant evolution note before reviewing\n- Reviewed current board-card operations against Task 1 of the no-editor-first workflow plan\n- Confirmed running board cards now expose the smallest routine control set directly from the card surface: prompt send via quick composer, Codex jump, and loop controls\n- Kept the review bounded and did not expand into spotlight, drawer, or cross-surface workflow changes\n- Moved the active slice forward to Task 2 audit because the remaining gaps now center on embedded runtime/log visibility rather than missing card-level operations\n\n## Failed or Deferred\n\n- No code changes were made in this review slice\n- Deferred deeper log/result redesign until Task 2 audit identifies the first smallest embedded-status gap\n\n## Decisions\n\n- Treat Task 1 as sufficiently bootstrapped once board cards themselves no longer force prompt sending back out to editor or terminal\n- Use the next loop to inspect runtime/log visibility rather than continuing to polish card-level actions\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n```text\nContinue the codex-loop from `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`. Stay on `task-plans/no-editor-first-workflows-task-plan.md` and do one bounded Task 2 audit focused on the first smallest runtime/log visibility gap that still pushes common checks out of cards or drawer.\n```\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
